  "decisions": [
    "Air temperature: site-specific sensor selection (T168 Hyytiala, Tair50HMP DE-HoH, Tair14PT Hohes-Holz, (TA_Z+TA_A)/2 El Palacio, TA_X HIDROMET, Vaisala HMP Rosalia)",
    "Precipitation: primary/fallback strategy (Precipacc_GPM/Precip Hyytiala, precip50/precip_back DE-HoH, P_RAIN El Palacio, P_RAIN_S1 HIDROMET)",
    "Soil moisture: shallowest available sensor (SWC at -4cm Hyytiala, SM at -10cm DE-HoH/Rosalia)",
    "Soil temperature: shallowest available sensor (Tsoil at -3.5cm Hyytiala, ST at -5cm DE-HoH, -10cm Rosalia)",
    "Temporal aggregation: all data aggregated to daily resolution (mean for temp/SWC, sum for precip, daily diff for accumulated precip)",
    "QC bounds: TA [-60,60], P [0,500], SWC [0,100], TS [-30,60] - values outside replaced with NaN",
    "Sensor heights from eLTER METHOD files and documentation (VERT_OFFSET in cm -> meters)",
    "Donana HIDROMET: 7 sub-stations with shared DEIMS siteID, individual lat/lon/elev from STATION file",
    "Germany DE-HoH large CSV files (438 MB SOATM, 1.4 GB SOHYD) processed in 1M-row chunks",
    "Hohes-Holz and Germany_DE-HoH are the same physical site in different data formats - both included",
    "Rosalia particle size data: normalized to sand/silt/clay excluding >2mm gravel fraction",
    "No unit conversions needed - all source data already in degC, mm, vol%"
  ]
